<p>
    <strong>Q1: Where can I catch brook trout closest to Salem?</strong><br>
    You can find brook trout in Detroit Lake, Breitenbush River, and several small creeks within an hour’s drive east of Salem.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q2: What’s the best bait or lure for brook trout?</strong><br>
    Brook trout respond well to small spinners (like Panther Martins) and live bait such as worms or salmon eggs. Fly anglers should try Woolly Buggers or Adams dry flies.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q3: When is the best time of day to fish for brook trout?</strong><br>
    Early morning and late evening are ideal, especially during warmer months when brook trout avoid bright sunlight.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q4: Can I keep brook trout I catch in Oregon?</strong><br>
    In most areas, yes—brook trout are non-native, so harvest is often encouraged. Always confirm bag limits for your fishing location.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q5: Are there any fly-fishing-only areas near Salem?</strong><br>
    Yes, sections of the North Santiam River and nearby tributaries have designated fly-fishing zones. Check ODFW’s official maps before heading out.
</p>
<p>
